<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-03T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-03T10:00:00-05:00" n="529" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/17: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-03T10:00:00-05:00">March 3, 1932—10
                                a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>76. Your 294, March 2, 11 a.m. If and when any notification is received
                            with regard to establishment of new regime in Manchuria, <pb facs="0600" n="496" xml:id="pg_496"/> inform Department but take no additional
                            action in absence of Department’s further instructions.</p>
                        <p>Instruct Mukden and Harbin.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>